The paper deals with algorithms for solving k-SUM problems, which are related to data structures and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses hashing techniques, which are related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper establishes a new time-space upper bound, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
